<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-609-192  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 609 192.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Iandamp;CS (Instrumentation andamp; Control Systems)  June 1990 v63 n6 p77(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Good planning and flexible systems lead to successful automation.andO;(includes related article on the six levels of operator interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lipka, Frank.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The 60,000 sq ft Milton, PA, facility of the Hoeganaes Corp is runby only 14 people.andP;  The plant, which manufactures ferrous powders,has a highly integrated system of programmable controllers,industrial operator interface workstations, automated guidedvehicles, stacker cranes, and minicomputer systems.andP;  Thisautomated system receives, verifies, and bar codes incoming rawmaterials; stages raw materials with the AGVs; moves raw materialsinto production using the AGVs, conveyors, and stacker cranes;manufacturers product flexibly and efficiently; permits qualitycontrol to verify product; packages and bar codes finishedproduct; and moves finished product to shipping.andP;  The system hastwo networks: a Genius bus for control command communications anda thin-wire Ethernet.andP;  The hardware and software are both modular.andO;The engineering for the control system was supplied by AdvancedAutomation Associates Inc. The quality of the finished product isexcellent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hoeganaes Corp. (automation)Advanced Automation Associates Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     ManufacturingControl SystemsFactory Management.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartphotograph.andO;Caption:   Programmable controllers' system. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>